HEADWORD: Negligible
<hw>Neg"li*gi*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧gligible</ets>, <ets>n⟦eacute⟧gligeable</ets>.]</ety>
<def>That may be neglected, disregarded, or left out of consideration;
too small or unimportant to be worthy of notice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Within very <qex>negligible</qex> limits of error.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir J. Herschel.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Negoce</ent>⟦br⟧
